an team, Cadillac, sponsored by General Motors. This isn=E2=80=99t just a m=
ilestone for the rapidly growing sport; it seems to be the first inroad tha=
t Trump 2.0 has made on the antitrust front, while also signaling a signifi=
cant media deal to come.<br/><br/>Liberty Media, which owns the commercial =
rights to F1, had previously blocked a proposed new team from <b>Michael An=
dretti</b>, sparking a Department of Justice investigation into possible an=
