>=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C100 Most Influential People in Artificial Intelligence=
=E2=80=9D list, even though <b>Sam Altman</b>=E2=80=99s company quickly den=
ied the accusation. At the time, it wasn=E2=80=99t clear whether Johansson =
had standing to sue over the alleged use of her voice from the movie <i>Her=
</i>=E2=80=94and she has yet to actually sue=E2=80=94but the letter ignited=
 a discussion about digital replicas, spurred legislative initiatives, and =
encouraged others to file lawsuits of their own. <br/><br/>Voice actor <b>P=
aul Lehrman</b>, for instance, is now fronting a class-action lawsuit in Ne=
w
York against Lovo Inc., an A.I. voice generator, for allegedly cloning his =
voice, alongside those of <b>Barack Obama</b>, <b>Conan O=E2=80=99Brien</b>=
, <b>Elton John</b>=E2=80=94and, yes, Johansson. <i>This</i> case, the firs=
t of its kind, just might force a court to reckon with the issues Johansson=
 teased.<br/><br/>Back in 2020, a Lovo employee cloaked as =E2=80=9CUser251=
99087=E2=80=9D navigated the freelance marketplace Fiverr.com to recruit ac=
tors. Lehrman, whose r=C3=A9sum=C3=A9 includes bit parts in TV shows like <=
i>Blue Bloods</i> and <i>New Amsterdam</i>, recorded 104 snippets for Lovo =
for $1,200, under the pretense of =E2=80=9Cacademic research.=E2=80=9D Lehr=
man wanted to know more, of course, but was told, he says, =E2=80=9CIt=E2=
=80=99s a confidential work in process sorry haha.=E2=80=9D<br/></td>
